# Normalize all text files to LF in both the index and the working
# tree. Eliminates the Windows-only "phantom diff" class where
# `git status` reports files as modified because cargo or rust-analyzer
# touched their mtime, while their content is byte-identical after
# line-ending normalization.
#
# `eol=lf` overrides `core.autocrlf` for any path matched by this rule,
# so this file is the source of truth — `git config core.autocrlf` no
# longer matters once `.gitattributes` is present.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files — never normalize line endings on these.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.zip   binary
*.gz    binary
*.exe   binary
*.dll   binary
*.pdb   binary
